        "subject": "LU-769 ptlrpc: conf-sanity test_23a failure",
        "message": "LU-769 ptlrpc: conf-sanity test_23a failure\n\nThe problem is clear: in original implementation, if a signal is already\nexistent, it will go for uninterruptible version of LWI. This causes the\nwaiting process will never be interrupted.\n\nI fixed this problem by removing check of cfs_signal_pending(), but it\nseems this piece of code needs more fixing.\n\nChange-Id: I28e9dc1969f1ab03800d1287392ab04459e8e1d5\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jay@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
